#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:761
msgid "Headphone and Master Mix Controls"
msgstr "Controles do Fone e da Mixagem Mestre"

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:770
msgid "The headphone and master mix knobs"
msgstr "Os botões de fone e mixagem mestre"

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:790
msgid "**Pre/Main Knob**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:773
msgid ""
"Allows you to control how much of the master output you hear in the "
":guilabel:`Headphones` output. It works like a crossfader between the stereo"
" Master and stereo :term:`PFL` signal. If the knob is set to the left, you "
"only hear the PFL signal, which is the usual position for prelistening "
"tracks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:778
msgid ""
"This can be used to practice DJing with only one stereo output and a set of "
"either speakers or headphones."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:781
msgid ""
"Additionally, this can be used to mix in headphones when you cannot hear the"
" speakers connected to the :guilabel:`Master` output and there are no booth "
"monitor speakers. Some DJs prefer to use this knob to mix in headphones all "
"the time, but many find it to be a difficult way to play. If there is only "
"one set of speakers and no booth monitors, you can avoid the need to mix in "
"headphones by setting up the speakers behind you so both you and your "
"audience can hear them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:789
msgid ""
"Don't forget to activate the :guilabel:`PFL` button on the deck you want to "
"listen to in your headphones."
msgstr "Não esqueça de ativar o botão :guilabel:`PFL` no deck que você quer escutar nos seus fones."

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:797
msgid "**Head-Split Button**"
msgstr "**Botão de Cueing Dividido**"

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:793
msgid ""
"If activated, two mono signals are sent to the headphone output instead of "
"one stereo signal. The master signal plays in the right channel, while the "
"cueing signal plays in the left channel. You can still adjust the "
":guilabel:`Pre/Main Knob` to control the mix of the master and cue signals "
"in the left channel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:801
msgid "**Balance Knob**"
msgstr "**Botão de Balanceamento**"

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:800
msgid ""
"This knob allows you to adjust the :term:`balance` (left/right orientation) "
"of the master output."
msgstr "Esse botão permite que você ajuste o :term:`balanceamento` (orientação esquerda/direita) da saída mestre."

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:830
msgid "**Master Knob**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:806
msgid ""
"The Master Gain Knob controls the gain applied to the Master output signal "
"that Mixxx sends to your sound card, Internet broadcasting servers, and "
"recorded mixes. Generally, this knob should not be adjusted. To change the "
"output volume, a gain control should be adjusted as close to the speakers as"
" possible for the best signal-to-noise ratio throughout your signal chain. "
"Ideally, the volume would only be adjusted by adjusting the gain on the "
"power amplifier. On active speakers, including computer speakers, studio "
"monitors, and PA systems that do not require a separate amplifier, this "
"means adjusting the gain on the speakers (which may be labeled \"Volume\")."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:816
msgid ""
"As a DJ, you may not have access to the power amplifier. In that case, "
"adjust the volume by adjusting the gain on the equipment closest to the "
"power amplifier that you have access to. Typically, this is a DJ mixer. If "
"you are not going through a mixer, adjust the gain of your sound card. If "
"your sound card does not have any controls on it (for example, for sound "
"cards built into computers), adjust the sound card settings with your "
":term:`OS <operating system>` mixer program. The Master Gain Knob in Mixxx "
"should be a last resort for adjusting volume."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:825
msgid ""
"**In no case should any part of the signal chain be clipping, indicated by a"
" level meter going into its red region or an LED labeled \"clipping\" "
"turning on.**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:829 ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:908
msgid ""
"For an explanation of why you should set your gains this way, see "
":ref:`Setting your levels properly (gain staging) <djing-gain-staging>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:841
msgid "**Head Gain Knob**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:833
msgid ""
"This knob controls the gain applied to the headphone output signal that "
"Mixxx sends to your sound card. Generally, this knob should not be adjusted."
" To adjust the volume in your headphones, adjust your sound card's gain on "
"the headphone output. Most external sound cards have a gain knob "
"specifically for the headphone jack. If you use an onboard sound card for "
"your headphones, adjust the gain control in your :term:`OS <operating "
"system>` mixer program. If your sound card only has one gain knob that "
"controls both the main output and the headphone output, then adjust the "
":guilabel:`Head Gain` knob in Mixxx to control the volume of your headphones"
" without affecting your main output."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:846
msgid "PFL/Headphone Button"
msgstr "Botão PFL/Fone"

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:855
msgid "The headphone buttons of both decks in the mixer"
msgstr "Os botões de fone dos decks no mixer"

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:857
msgid ""
"The headphone button is also known as the :term:`pre-fader listen or PFL "
"<PFL>` button and allows you to use headphone cueing. That is, it allows you"
" to hear the track you will play next in your headphones before your "
"audience hears it. This helps you plan when to start the next track and "
"manipulate it to make it blend better with the currently playing track (for "
"example, by synchronizing the beats, setting a loop, or using EQs). Pressing"
" the PFL button plays the track on the headphone output at full volume "
"regardless of the position of the crossfader or the deck’s line fader. To "
"play a track in your headphones but not have the audience hear it, press the"
" PFL button and move the crossfader all the way to the opposite side of the "
"deck or turn the deck’s volume fader all the way down."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:869
msgid ""
"Headphone cueing is only available if you have configured a Headphone Output"
" in :menuselection:`Preferences --> Sound Hardware`."
msgstr "Cueing no fone só é disponível se você configurou uma Saída de Fone em :menuselection:`Preferências --> Hardware de Som`."

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:872
msgid ""
"If you use an external hardware mixer, plug your headphones into that rather"
" than your sound card. Use the headphone buttons on the mixer rather than "
"the buttons in Mixxx."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:879
msgid "Equalizers and Gain Knobs"
msgstr "Equalizadores e Botões de Ganho"

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:888
msgid "EQ Controls"
msgstr "Controles de EQ"

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:909
#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1055
msgid "**Gain Knob**"
msgstr "**Botão de Ganho**"

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:891
msgid ""
"The gain knob allows you to adjust the gain applied to the deck. Use this to"
" compensate for the differences in recording levels between tracks. In "
"general, you should adjust this knob so that the track's :term:`level meter`"
" stays around the top of the green region with the loudest parts of the "
"track (the transients) briefly going into the yellow region. **Do NOT turn "
"the Gain Knob up so much that the level meter is in the red region. At this "
"point the track is clipping, which sounds bad and could damage equipment.**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:899
msgid ""
"By default, Mixxx automatically applies an additional ReplayGain so tracks "
"have approximately equal loudness at unity gain. Your tracks must be "
":ref:`analyzed <getting-started-analyze-library>` to take advantage of this "
"feature. When an unanalyzed track is loaded, Mixxx calculates its ReplayGain"
" value, but will not apply a newly calculated ReplayGain value to a track "
"after it has already started playing (to avoid a sudden change in the gain "
"of a playing track)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:919
msgid "**EQ Knobs**"
msgstr "**Botões de EQ**"

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:912
msgid ""
"The low, mid, and high EQ knobs allow you to change the filters of the "
"audio. This allows you to selectively reduce or boost certain frequency "
"ranges of the audio."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:916
msgid ""
"Be careful not to raise the EQs so much that the signal clips, indicated by "
"a :term:`level meter` being in the red region. See :ref:`Setting your levels"
" properly (gain staging) <djing-gain-staging>` for a more detailed "
"explanation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:926
msgid "**Kill Switches**"
msgstr "**Botões Matar**"

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:922
msgid ""
"The small boxes next to each EQ knob are called :term:`kills <kill switch>`."
" Hold these buttons to fully remove that frequency range. Short click on the"
" buttons for latching. When in Latch mode, click again to restore the "
"frequency range. If the Kill switches do not work as expected, check the "
"high/low shelf EQ settings in the preferences."
msgstr "As caixas pequenas ao lado de cada botão de EQ são chamadas de :term:`botões de matar <kill switch>`. Segure esses botões para remover totalmente essa extensão de frequência. Clique rapidamente nos botões para manter. Quando ele estiver nesse modo mantendo, clique de novo para restaurar a extensão de frequência. Se os botões matar não funcionam como esperado, verifique as configurações da faixa de EQ nas preferências."

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:928
msgid ""
"You can customize the EQ settings in :menuselection:`Preferences --> "
"Equalizer`."
msgstr "Você pode personalizar as configurações de EQ em :menuselection:`Preferências --> Equalizador`."

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:934
msgid "Crossfader"
msgstr "Crossfader"

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:943
msgid "The crossfader section of the mixer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:945
msgid ""
"The :term:`crossfader` determines the actual volume of each deck when moving"
" the slider from left to right. If both decks are playing and the crossfader"
" is in its default center position, then you will hear both decks. Right-"
"clicking on the crossfader will reset the slider to its default position."
msgstr "O :term:`crossfader` determina o volume real de cada deck ao mover o deslizante da esquerda para a direita. Se ambos os decks estiverem tocando e o crossfader estiver na sua posição padrão central, então você vai ouvir ambas os decks. Clicar com o lado direito no crossfader vai resetar o deslizante para a sua posição padrão"

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:950
msgid ""
"You can reverse the configuration of the crossfader, so that the right deck "
"is on the left end of the crossfader and vice versa. This is also known as "
"*Hamster Style*. To adjust the crossfader to your style of mixing, go to "
":menuselection:`Preferences --> Crossfader`."
msgstr "Você pode inverter a configuração do crossfader, para que o deck da direita seja no final da esquerda do crossfader e vice-versa. Isso também é conhecido como *Estilo Hamster*. Para ajustar o crossfader para o seu estilo de mixagem, vá para :menuselection:`Preferências --> Crossfader`."

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:955
msgid ""
"Using the :ref:`AutoDJ <djing-auto-dj>` feature in Mixxx, you can automate "
"the crossfade between the decks."
msgstr "Usando a funcionalidade de :ref:`AutoDJ <djing-auto-dj>` do Mixxx, você pode automatizar a transição entre faixas."

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:961
msgid "The Sampler Section"
msgstr "A Seção Sampler"

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:970
msgid "A sample deck"
msgstr "Um deck de samples"

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:972
msgid ""
"Samplers are miniature decks. They allow you to play short samples and "
"jingles but also additional tracks in your mix. They come with a small "
"overview waveform and a limited number of controls. All controls work just "
"like on the regular decks, see :ref:`interface-decks`."
msgstr "Samplers são decks em miniatura. Eles permitem que você toque amostras curtas e jingles mas também faixas adicionais em sua mixagem. Eles vem com uma visão global das ondas e um número de controles limitados. Todos os controles funcionam como se eles fossem decks normais, veja :ref:`interface-decks`."

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:977
msgid ""
"The Sampler section can be **hidden** in the :ref:`Mixxx user interface "
"<interface-overview>`. Click the :ref:`SAMPLER <interface-expansion-"
"buttons>` button, or use the specific :ref:`appendix-shortcuts` to show or "
"hide the section."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:983
msgid "Waveform Display"
msgstr "Mostrador de Ondas"

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:986
msgid ""
"The waveform shows the various markers within the track as well as the "
"waveform envelope of the entire track. Clicking somewhere on the waveform "
"allows you to jump to an arbitrary position in the track."
msgstr "O mostrador de ondas mostra vários marcadores na faixa e também as ondas de toda a faixa. Clicar em algum lugar das ondas permite que você pule para uma posição arbitrária na faixa."

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:991
msgid "While mixing, some additional markers can appear on the waveforms:"
msgstr "Enquanto mixando, alguns marcadores adicionais podem aparecer nas ondas:"

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:993
msgid ""
"**Position marker**: A vertical line indicates the playback point of the "
"sample deck."
msgstr "**Marcador de Posição**: Uma linha vertical indica o ponto de reprodução do deck de samples."

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1003
msgid "**Track Artist/Title**"
msgstr "**Artista/Título da Faixa**"

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1002
msgid ""
"The artist and title of the track that was loaded into a sampler deck is "
"displayed here."
msgstr "O artista e o título da faixa que foi carregado em um deck do sampler é mostrado aqui."

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1006
msgid ""
"The number at the top right is the effective :term:`BPM` of the track. Tap "
"the BPM to set the BPM to the speed you are tapping."
msgstr "O número no topo direito é o :term:`BPM` efetivo da faixa. Toque o BPM para definir o BPM para a velocidade que você estiver tocando"

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1011
msgid ""
"The buttons grid next to the waveform overview allow you to configure the "
"sampler deck. Starting from the top-left and moving counterclockwise the "
"buttons are as follows:"
msgstr "A grade de botões perto da visão geral das ondas permite que você configure o deck de samples. Começando do topo esquerdo e movendo sentido anti-horário os botões são os seguintes:"

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1020
msgid "Clicking this button ejects the track from the deck."
msgstr "Clicar nesse botão ejeta a faixa do deck"

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1023
#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1122
msgid "**Mix Orientation Toggle**"
msgstr "**Alternar Orientação da Mixagem**"

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1023
msgid "This control determines the sampler input's mix orientation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1026
msgid ""
":term:`Keylock <key lock>` locks the track's pitch so that adjustments to "
"its tempo via the rate slider do not affect its pitch."
msgstr "A :term:`Trava de Tom <key lock>` trava o pitch da faixa fazendo com que ajustamentos no tempo usando o deslizante do pitch não afetem o pitch. "

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1030
msgid "Sample Deck Controls"
msgstr "Controles do Deck de Samples"

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1036
msgid "**Play/Pause button**"
msgstr "**Botão Tocar/Pausar**"

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1033
msgid ""
"Clicking the button always starts playback from the :term:`cue point <cue>`."
" If playback is already enabled the play position will jump back to the "
":term:`cue point <cue>`. Right-clicking on the button will stop playback and"
" seek the play position to the beginning of the sample."
msgstr "O clique no botão começa sempre a reprodução do :term:`ponto cue <cue>`. Se a reprodução já está ativada, a posição de reprodução vai pular de volta para o :term:`ponto cue <cue>`. Um clique com o lado direito vai parar a reprodução e vai colocar a posição de reprodução no começo da sample."

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1039
msgid "**Sync Button**"
msgstr "**Botão Sincronizar**"

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1039
msgid ""
"Syncs the Sampler deck to a regular deck, as described in :ref:`interface-"
"rate`."
msgstr "Sincroniza o deck de samples com um deck normal, como descrito em :ref:`interface-rate`."

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1041
msgid ""
"**Left-Click**: Changes the :term:`rate` of the track so that the "
":term:`BPM` and :term:`phase` of the track matches the sync target."
msgstr "**Clique com o lado esquerdo**: Muda a :term:`taxa` da faixa para que o :term:`BPM` e a :term:`fase` da faixa igualem o alvo de sincronização."

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1043
msgid ""
"**Right-Click**: Only changes the :term:`rate` of the track to match the "
"sync target but does not adjust the :term:`phase`."
msgstr "**Clique com o lado direito**: Apenas muda a :term:`taxa` da faixa para igualar ao do alvo de sincronização mas naõ ajusta a :term:`fase`."

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1048
msgid "**Hotcue Controls**"
msgstr "**Controles de Hotcue**"

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1047
msgid ""
"To jump in between different parts of a sample, you can use these numbered "
"hotcue buttons."
msgstr "Para pular entre diferentes partes da sample, você pode usar estes botões de hotcues numeradas."

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1052
msgid "**PFL/Headphone Button**"
msgstr "**Botão PFL/Fone**"

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1051
msgid ""
"If active, the :term:`pre-fader listen or PFL <PFL>` button allows you to "
"listen to the track in your headphones."
msgstr "Se ativo, o botão :term:`pre-fader listen ou PFL <PFL>` permite que você escute à faixa nos seus fones."

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1055
msgid "Allows you to adjust the gain applied to the track."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1058
msgid "**Level Meter**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1058
msgid "Shows the level of the signal and can be adjusted with the Gain knob."
msgstr "Mostra o nivel do sinal e mode ser ajustado com o botão de Ganho"

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1061
msgid ""
"The slider allows you to change the speed of the sample. Right-clicking on "
"the slider will reset the tempo to its original value."
msgstr "Esse deslizante permite que você mude a velocidade da sample. Clicar com o lado direito no deslizante vai resetar o tempo para o valor original"

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1067
msgid "The Effects Section"
msgstr "A Seção Efeitos"

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1075
msgid "An effect unit"
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1077
msgid ""
"Mixxx comes with some built in sound effects that can be chained together in"
" effect units. Effect units can be freely assigned to different decks as "
"well as other inputs. The buttons for routing decks to effect units are in "
"the :ref:`interface-decks`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1082
msgid ""
"The :ref:`effects` chapter has a more detailed explanation of the effects "
"system."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1088
msgid "The Microphone Section"
msgstr "A Seção Microfone"

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1100
msgid "The Microphone section"
msgstr "A seção Microfone"

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1102
msgid ""
"The microphone section is **hidden** in the default :ref:`Mixxx user "
"interface <interface-overview>`. Click the :ref:`MIC <interface-expansion-"
"buttons>` button in the mixer section, or use the specific :ref:`appendix-"
"shortcuts` to show or hide the section."
msgstr "A seção microfone é **escondida** por padrão na :ref:`interface do usuário do Mixxx <interface-overview>`. Clique no botão :ref:`MIC <interface-expansion-buttons>` na seção do mixer, ou use os específicos :ref:`appendix-shortcuts` para mostrar ou ocultar essa seção."

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1107
msgid ""
"The :ref:`microphones` chapter has detailed instructions for setting up "
"microphones with various hardware."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1111
msgid "Microphone Controls"
msgstr "Controles de Microfone"

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1117
msgid "**Talk Button**"
msgstr "**Botão Falar**"

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1114
msgid ""
"Hold this button and talk to mix the microphone input into the Mixxx master "
"output. Short click on the button for latching. This is handy for talking "
"for an extended period, for example when :ref:`streaming <live-"
"broadcasting>` a radio show. When in Latch mode, click again to mute the "
"microphone input."
msgstr "Segure este botão e fale para mixar a entrada do microfone com a saída mestre do Mixxx. Clique rapidamente o botão para manter. Isso é conveniente para falar por um período extenso, por exemplo quando :ref:`streaming <live-broadcasting>` um show de rádio. Quando ele estiver nesse modo mantendo, clique de novo para abafar a entrada de microfone."

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1120
msgid ""
"This control determines the microphone input's mix orientation. Either to "
"the left side of crossfader, to the right side or to the center (default). "
"Clicking cycles through all the options."
msgstr "Esse controle determina a orientação da mixagem da entrada do microfone. Para o lado esquerda do crossfader, para o lado direito ou para o centro (padrão). Clicar alterna entre todas as opções."

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1125
msgid "**Microphone Volume Meter**"
msgstr "**Medidor do Volume do Microfone**"

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1125
msgid "This displays the microphone volume input signal strength."
msgstr "Isso mostra o volume da potência do sinal de entrada do microfone."

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1129
msgid "**Microphone Gain Knob**"
msgstr "**Botão de Ganho do Microfone**"

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1128
msgid ""
"Use this knob to adjust the gain of the microphone output. Try to keep the "
"volume at a reasonable level to avoid signal clipping."
msgstr "Use este botão para ajustar o ganho da entrada do microfone. Tente manter o volume em um nível razoável para evitar clipagem."

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1134
msgid "Preview Deck Section"
msgstr "Seção do Deck de Pré-Escuta"

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1146
msgid "The Preview Deck with a track loaded"
msgstr "O Deck de Pré-escuta com uma faixa carregada"

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1148
msgid ""
"The Preview Deck is a special deck that allows you to pre-listen to tracks "
"in the headphones before using them in your mix. Pre-listening a track does "
"not change the tracks's :guilabel:`Played` state as well as the play counter"
" and is not logged in the :ref:`History <library-history>`. Press "
":kbd:`CTRL` + :kbd:`4` (Windows/Linux) or :kbd:`CMD` + :kbd:`4` (Mac) to "
"display the Preview Deck."
msgstr "O Deck de Pré-escuta é um deck especial que permite que você pré-escute faixas nos fones antes de usá-las no seu mix. Pré-escutar faixas não muda o estado de :guilabel:`Tocada` da faixa e o contador de reproduções também não será mudado e essa reprodução não será gravado no :ref:`Histórico <library-history>`. Pressione :kbd:`CTRL` + :kbd:`4` (Windows/Linux) ou :kbd:`CMD` + :kbd:`4` (Mac) para mostrar o Deck de Pré-escuta."

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1154
msgid "The features in detail:"
msgstr "As funcionalidades em detalhe:"

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1156
msgid ""
"**Track Artist/Title**: The artist and title of the track is displayed here."
" This is the same listed under the :guilabel:`Track` and :guilabel:`Title` "
"column in the Mixxx library. This information is initially loaded from the "
"track's :term:`metadata`."
msgstr "**Artista/Título da Faixa**: O artista e o título da faixa é mostrado aqui. É o mesmo listado na coluna :guilabel:`Artista` e :guilabel:`Título` na biblioteca do Mixxx. Essa informação é inicialmente carregada dos :term:`metadados` da faixa."

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1161
msgid ""
"**Eject Track button**: Clicking this button ejects the track from the deck."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1164
msgid ""
"**Play/Pause button**: Clicking the button starts and pauses the playback. "
"Right-clicking on the button will stop playback and seek the play position "
"to the beginning of the tracks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../chapters/user_interface.rst:1169
msgid ""
"**Waveform overview**: Shows the various markers (Cues, Hotcues) within the "
"track as well as the waveform envelope of the entire track. Clicking "
